        "type": "User",
        "site_admin": false,
        "name": null,
        "patch_url": null
      },
      "body": "I'm convinced this will not break things and I like this more after fiddling with the bits.\n\nBut feels like the original check combined with line 43 was already sufficient for checking we are not able to cross limbs when trying to collect bits from the scalar.\n\nOne such case could be: `offset = 31`.\n\nWith the original check:\nRHS: `offset >> 6 = 0`\nLHS: `(31 + count - 1) >> 6` => `count < 34` so that RHS == LHS.\n\nBut line 43 already guarantee that `count <= 32`. Similar for the other limbs.",
      "created_at": "2026-04-22T22:54:00Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-22T22:54:00Z",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1/pull/1845#discussion_r3127312863",
      "author_association": "NONE",
